President Joe Biden will be hosting Taoiseach of Ireland, Leo Varadkar, for a bilateral meeting and St. Patrick's Day celebration at the White House on March 17. The purpose of the meeting is to reaffirm the strong partnership between the United States and Ireland and discuss their shared commitment to supporting Ukraine against Russia's aggression. The leaders will also talk about their cooperation on global issues and express their support for the Belfast/Good Friday Agreement, as it approaches its 25th anniversary. Vice President Kamala Harris and Second Gentleman Douglas Emhoff will also be hosting a breakfast for the Taoiseach and Mr. Matthew Barrett at the Naval Observatory.